/div></div><div id="recipetools" class="constantco-widget section-recipetools" data-app-resource-id="97410" data-type="recipetools" data-params="mobile_breakpoint=821"></div><div id="responsive-tabs" class="responsive-tabs responsive-tabs--2"><ul class="responsive-tabs__tabs"><li class="responsive-tabs__tab is-active"> <a href="#recipe-ingredients">Ingredients</a></li><li class="responsive-tabs__tab"> <a href="#recipe-method">Method</a></li></ul><div class="responsive-tabs__panes"> <section id="recipe-ingredients" class="responsive-tabs__pane is-active"><h2 class="responsive-tabs__pane-title">Ingredients</h2><div class="ingredients-list"><div class="ingredients-list__content"><ul class="ingredients-list__group"><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="1 small red onion, very finely chopped">1 small red onion, very finely chopped</li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="small bunch dill, most roughly chopped">small bunch dill, most roughly chopped</li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="2 tsp fresh or creamed horseradish">2 tsp fresh or creamed <a href="/glossary/horse-radish" class="ingredients-list__glossary-link" data-tooltip-content="#ingredients-glossary &gt; article" data-tooltip-width="350" data-tooltip-hide-delay="200" data-tooltip-flyout="true">horseradish</a><span class="ingredients-list__glossary-element" id="ingredients-glossary"><article id="node-6909541" role="main" class="node node-glossary-item node-teaser node-teaser clearfix main row grid-padding"><div class="node-image"> <a href="/glossary/horse-radish"><img src="//www.bbcgoodfood.com/sites/default/files/styles/bbcgf_thumbnail_search/public/glossary-item/glossary-image/2017/11/horseradish-root.jpg?itok=yjxynaCi" width="100" height="100" alt="Horseradish root on a wooden chopping board" title="Horseradish" /></a></div><h2 class="node-title node-glossary-title"><a href="/glossary/horse-radish">Horseradish</a></h2> <span class="fonetic text-style-alt">hors rad-ish</span><p>Horseradish root is larger than an ordinary radish, and has a hot, peppery flavour.</p><p>It…</p> </article></span></li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="good squeeze lemon juice">good squeeze lemon juice</li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="100ml soured cream">100ml soured cream</li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="200g smoked salmon">200g smoked salmon</li></ul></div></div> </section> <section id="recipe-method" class="responsive-tabs__pane"><h2 class="responsive-tabs__pane-title">Method</h2><div class="method"><ol class="method__list"><li class="method__item" itemprop="recipeInstructions"><p>Tip the onion and chopped dill into a bowl with the horseradish and lemon juice. Stir through the soured cream, season with a pinch of salt and generous grinding of pepper, and mix well. <i>Can be made a day ahead and kept in the fridge</i>.</p></li><li class="method__item" itemprop="recipeInstructions"><p>Arrange the salmon on a board or plate, scatter with the remaining dill fronds and serve with a grinding of black pepper and the sauce alongside.</p></li></ol></div> <footer class="recipe-info"><div class="recipe-info__publication">Recipe from Good Food magazine, <a href="/search/recipes/date/1354320000" class="text-style-alt">December 2012</a></div> <a class="recipe-info__magazine-ad" href=" https://www.buysubscriptions.com/print/bbc-good-food-magazine-subscription?promo=GFBS718&style=Brand&utm_medium=brandsite&utm_source=bbcgoodfood.com&utm_campaign=recipe_GFBS718_Brand&utm_content=recipe-banner" rel="external" onclick="Drupal.GFAnalytics.trackEvent(['Magazines', 'subscribe', 'Recipe' ])"> <img src="https://www.bbcgoodfood.com/sites/default/files/magazine/gf_aug18_337x109.jpg" alt="BBC GoodFood Magazine" /> </a> </footer> </section></div></div> <section id="block-bbcgf-search-views-bbcgf-cc-rel-recipes" class="sect